Former Salomon Brothers managing director and head trader Thomas Murphy was
ordered to pay Dollars 300,000 and barred from taking part in US Treasury
auction bids, the US Securities and Exchange Commission said. The SEC took
action against Mr Murphy over a Treasury bidding scandal, alleging he had
submitted false customer bids in three auctions of Treasury securities and
caused Salomon to create false books and records.
