<HEADLINE>
FT  31 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Buckingham Pounds 6m disposal
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Buckingham International, the property, hotels and nursing group which
announced interim pre-tax losses of Pounds 62.5m and a breach of banking
covenants in September, is to raise Pounds 6.4m with the sale of its nursing
homes division.
The division, which is being sold to Unicare, a private nursing homes
operator, produced profits before interest of Pounds 1.1m for the year ended
November 1. The business has a book value of Pounds 6.7m.
The group also announced that the first in its planned disposals to reduce
debt of Pounds 95.5m had been delayed. The sale of its Portuguese hotels
subsidiary which owns and operates the Holiday Inn in Lisbon, failed to meet
its December 29 deadline. The company said the buyer was still keen, but
more time was needed to negotiate with holders of Buckingham International's
loan stock 1995, part of the security for which is the Lisbon Holiday Inn.
The deadline to complete the sale of Morlaix de Portugal Investimentos
Hoteleiros e Turisticos had been extended to February 28.
