<HEADLINE>
FT  31 DEC 93 / British Rail plans new services
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
British Rail yesterday announced plans for new passenger services and
shorter journey times for its summer 1994 timetable, the last it will
control before privatisation begins next year.
The improvements include new direct services from Manchester Airport to
Glasgow and Edinburgh. Cardiff will be linked via Bristol to London Waterloo
to connect with Channel tunnel services.
New services will include Maidstone to Gatwick Airport, and West Worthing to
Eastbourne via Brighton. BR says it hopes to provide more trains on popular
routes, and to open more than 10 new stations.
</TEXT>
