FT  31 DEC 93 / Pumping ends today at Durham colliery
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRIS TIGHE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Pumping at disused Murton colliery in County Durham is to end today after
detailed technical discussions between British Coal and the National Rivers
Authority, the river pollution watchdog.
The NRA said yesterday that it was satisfied that the end of pumping at
Murton, which ceased production two years ago, would not cause water
pollution. But British Coal, which has been spending about Pounds 6m
annually on pumping in the Durham field, will retain mine shafts at the
former Dawdon and Easington collieries, to which Murton's abandoned workings
are linked, so pumping could resume if required.
