<HEADLINE>
FT  31 DEC 93 / Back to Britain
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By IAN HAMILTON FAZEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The US is giving Little America back to Britain, Ian Hamilton Fazey writes.
The Burtonwood airbase at Warrington in Cheshire will be formally handed
over in April. At its peak, shortly after the second world war, Burtonwood's
600 acres housed 18,000 Americans, making it the biggest single site for US
personnel in Britain.
The last symbol of those days is a 2m sq ft warehouse leased from the
Ministry of Defence for more than half a century. The US is spending Pounds
2m refurbishing it, having vacated it in October.
The site is to be developed as a business park for inward investors. Its
location in what became known as Little America is to be promoted all over
the US to attract companies, playing on wartime memories.
</TEXT>
