abroad, the cabinet said, Reuter reports from Rome.
Italian government bonds remain subject to the 12.5 per cent withholding tax
on coupon payments. Italy has a large secondary government bond market which
trades about L13,000bn worth of paper a day.
However, increasing demand for Italian paper from foreign investors has
caused a boom in centres such as London.
