<HEADLINE>
FT  30 DEC 93 / UK Company News: Shield makes acquisition
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID BLACKWELL
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Shield Group, the holding company that owns Stickley Kent, the auctioneer
and property insolvency specialist, has acquired Kamco Computer Systems, a
leading maker of customised personal computers.
Mr Norman Mazure, the chairman who owns 30 per cent of Shield, said
yesterday that the company paid less than Pounds 50,000 cash for Kamco,
which is expected to report turnover this year of Pounds 4m.
Kamco, founded five years ago and based in Uxbridge, sells its products only
through mail order and advertising. Mr Mazure said the mail order market for
PCs was worth about Pounds 1.2bn a year in the UK and was shared between 600
companies. He believed Kamco to be about sixth or seventh biggest.
Shield intends to keep Kamco's existing management team, including Mr Zygi
Kamasa, the founder and managing director, and Mr Gary Russell, operations
director.
</TEXT>
