<HEADLINE>
FT  30 DEC 93 / Letters to the Editor: Bank not left homeless if it never
had a home
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From Mr P J PACE O'SHEA
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, I do not think that your headline, 'Forerunner of European central bank
is left homeless' (December 29) is true. It would have been left homeless if
it had a home and then left it, for whatever reason, with nowhere to go.
I suspect there is a little wry amusement at the bank's initial difficulties
in that headline. But we have lost this one for good and it would be best to
learn to live with it.
P J Pace O'Shea,
45 Fellows Road,
London NW3 3DX
</TEXT>
<XX>
