<HEADLINE>
FT  29 DEC 93 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Last week we reported already that pepper prices had started to improve.
During this week the upward trend continued both for white and black pepper.
A recent survey in the far east reveals that white pepper stocks in
Indonesia are much too low to cover the requirements for the next 7/8 months
to come before the new crop will be available. It is therefore not so
surprising that prices recovered from Dollars 2400 cif, a fortnight ago to
about Dollars 3000 cif, today. A slight recovery in the
demand(shortcovering) triggered the market already. Since not much material
from other sources may be expected the supply position will remain very
tight. Black pepper prices also recovered quickly from their lows (Dollars
1250 cif) to about Dollars 1600 cif,(today) all origins tended much firmer
from the moment some demand came in from non traditional consuming markets.
</TEXT>
