</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Australian Mutual Provident Society (AMP), Australia's biggest insurance and
investment institution, plans to tap the emerging consumer demand for
insurance in Asia by investing in an Indonesian life insurance concern,
AP-DJ reports from Sydney.
AMP said it would enter into a transaction to invest more than ADollars 100m
(Dollars 65m) to buy 40 per cent of Panin Life Insurance, the largest life
insurance operation in terms of assets in Indonesia, and establish a joint
venture with Panin Life.
Panin Life is owned by Panin Bank, one of the largest privately held banks
in the country.
